We have falcon 500 motors as drive motors for our swerve drive with phoenix6 firmware. I’m trying to tune the drive to make it more accurate for autonomous commands, so I created a sysid project to generate the logs, pushed it to the robot, and ran the tests. Now I need help understanding the results and how to convert them for use with phoenix6. Here’s the analysis of one of the motors, the other 3 were very close to this:

image1004×819 109 KB

For phoenix6, kV is expressed as volts/rotation. What I logged for sysid was velocity in m/s and position in meters. The kV is stupid high… right now we have it at 0.113. Do I need to convert it back to volts per rotation from 2.943 volts per meter? Just doing a quick calculation I get 0.21 volts per rotation, which is still almost double but considerably better than 2.943.

Am I looking at this right? Same thing for kA?

And then I’m also not sure what to do about the Feedback values. Again, a kP of 1.4658 is WAY too high. Do I do the same conversion?
